    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-12-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-12-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="370"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d370">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">695A.0024/12–2952</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Director of the Office of
                        United Nations Political and Security Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_WDW1"
                            >Wainhouse</persName>)</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d370fn1">Copies of this memorandum went to <persName
                            corresp="#p_BDKE1">Bruce</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_MHF1"
                            >Matthews</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_HJD1">Hickerson</persName>,
                            <persName corresp="#p_AJM1">Allison</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_JUA1">Johnson</persName>, and <persName corresp="#p_HL1"
                            >Henkin</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" type="conversation-or-meeting-date"
                            when="1952-12-29">December 29, 1952</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>Subject:</head>
                    <item>Korea: Prisoners of War.</item>
                </list>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>Participants:</head>
                    <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">John Foster Dulles</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_WDW1">David W. Wainhouse</persName>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <pb facs="0754" n="720" xml:id="pg_720"/>
                <p>In a conversation the other day which I had with Mr. <persName corresp="#p_DJF1"
                        >Dulles</persName>, he referred to a visit paid him in New York by Mr.
                        <persName corresp="#p_MVKK1">Krishna Menon</persName> of the Indian
                    Delegation. Mr. <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName> said that Mr.
                        <persName corresp="#p_MVKK1">Menon</persName> sought to secure concessions
                    from him on the American stand on the prisoner of war question. Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName> said that he gave no encouragement
                    whatsoever to Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MVKK1">Menon</persName> on this
                    matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WDW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">David W. Wainhouse</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
